  "prompt": "Which are the best stem cell research labs in India for doing masters dissertion project on stem cell?",
  "response": "India has several prestigious institutes and labs that are renowned for their work in stem cell research. Here are some of the best institutions where you can consider doing your master's dissertation project:\n\n1. **National Centre for Cell Science (NCCS), Pune**: NCCS is a well-known research institution for cellular and molecular biology. It has various research programs focusing on stem cells.\n\n2. **National Institute of Immunology (NII), New Delhi**: NII is renowned for its research in immunology, including stem cell biology. It provides great opportunities for research at postgraduate levels.\n\n3. **Institute for Stem Cell Biology and Regenerative Medicine (InStem), Bangalore**: InStem focuses on research in stem cell biology, regenerative medicine, and related areas. It's a part of the Bangalore Life Science Cluster, which includes NCBS and C-CAMP.\n\n4. **Centre for Stem Cell Research (CSCR), Vellore**: Located at the Christian Medical College (CMC) campus, CSCR is involved in cutting-edge stem cell research and translational studies. \n\n5. **Jawaharlal Nehru Centre for Advanced Scientific Research (JNCASR), Bangalore**: JNCASR offers a conducive environment for research in various scientific domains, including stem cell biology.\n\n6. **National Institute of Cell Science and Tissue Engineering (NICSTE), Kolkata**: NICSTE offers research opportunities and projects in stem cell biology and tissue engineering.\n\n7. **Indian Institute of Science (IISc), Bangalore**: IISc is one of India's premier institutes for higher education and research in science and engineering. Its Centre for Neuroscience, Molecular Reproduction, and Development Genetics lab conduct significant stem cell research.\n\nThese institutions have state-of-the-art facilities and experienced faculty, making them ideal for conducting master's dissertation projects in stem cell research. Make sure to research each institution\u2019s specific programs and application requirements to find the best fit for your interests and academic goals.",
